<PortfolioLayout
  title="Roll by ADP"
  desc="Chat bot with AI as your HCM personal assistant"
>
  <div class="min-h-80">
    <h2
      class={`mt-4 text-3xl xl:text-4xl font-display uppercase ${VARIANT_MAPS["roll"].h1}`}
    >
      Pre<span class="font-variants-01-ls">f</span><span
        class="font-variants-01">a</span
      >ce: <span class="font-variants-01">R</span>oll
    </h2>
    <h3
      class={`mb-4 text-xl xl:text-2xl font-display ${VARIANT_MAPS["roll"].h2}`}
    >
      UX, UI, Design Sys<span class="font-variants-01">t</span>em
    </h3>
    <div class="mb-4 xs:mb-8 grid gap-4 xs:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <p class="lg:text-xl font-semibold">
        Combined business ideas with small business owner needs to create a new
        way to run payroll and manage <abbr title="Human Capital Management"
          >HCM</abbr
        > on the go with a mobile first approach from concept to component library.
      </p>
      <p class="lg:text-lg">
        Roll by ADP is a self service app that allows business owners to run
        payroll and manage <abbr title="Human Capital Management">HCM</abbr> through
        a chat bot with a sophisticated suite of <abbr title="Machine Learning"
          >ML</abbr
        > algorithms and <abbr title="Artificial Intelligence">AI</abbr>. Our
        workflow engine is based on event sourcing which captures actions and
        stores it in sequence. We apply this to a few user interfaces on mobile
        devices and desktop.
      </p>
      <p class="lg:text-lg">
        There are a wide array of attributes that can be applied to a manager or
        employee. They can be mixed and matched depending on the company,
        location and organization structure. What payment method do we use for
        our employees? Did they get a mid-cycle rise? How many hours did they
        work? Did they have overtime or sick time?
      </p>
    </div>
    <section
      class="grid gap-4 place-items-center xs:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 md:grid-rows-2 lg:grid-cols-8 lg:grid-rows-8 mb-4"
    >
